claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A clinical table comparing two vaccine groups (N=279,400 vs. N=395,852) on primary and secondary outcomes, including PCR-confirmed influenza (overall, type A, type B) and various hospitalization endpoints, with rate ratios, hazard ratios, vaccine effectiveness percentages, confidence intervals, and P values. The table presents vaccine efficacy and hospitalization outcomes but does not provide any information about antigenic matching to WHO- or FDA-selected flu strains, and therefore does not support the claim. Note: None
